<div class="page-container">
  <!-- ═══ HEADER ═══ -->
  <div class="header-content">
    <div class="tag">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
    <h1>O'Reilly Automotive (ORLY) Intrinsic Value</h1>
    <div class="meta-info">Published March 18, 2026 • By <span class="accent">Westmount Research</span></div>
  </div>

  <p>O'Reilly Automotive is a compounding machine, systematically growing its footprint and returning massive amounts of capital through aggressive share buybacks. However, unlike high-growth tech, retail auto parts is a mature industry. The question is: at what price does this predictable cash flow become a good investment?</p>

  <p>Below is a transparent, step-by-step discounted cash flow (DCF) valuation using FY2025 actuals. No black boxes. Just cash flows and math.</p>

  <!-- ═══ VERDICT CARD ═══ -->
  <div class="verdict-card">
    <div class="verdict-title">Estimated Fair Value</div>
    <div class="verdict-price">${roundedIV.toFixed(2)}</div>
    <div class="verdict-badge" style={`background-color: ${verdictColor}20; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}40;`}>
      {verdict}
    </div>

    <div class="verdict-context">
      <div>
        <span class="vc-label">Current Price:</span>
        <span class="vc-value">${currentPrice.toFixed(2)}</span>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="vc-label">Margin of Safety:</span>
        <span class="vc-value" style={`color: ${marginOfSafety > 0 ? '#10b981' : '#ef4444'}`}>
          {marginOfSafety > 0 ? '+' : ''}{marginOfSafety.toFixed(1)}%
        </span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ METHODOLOGY & ASSUMPTIONS ═══ -->
  <h2>The Assumptions</h2>
  <p>A DCF is only as good as its inputs. We start with O'Reilly's FY2025 Free Cash Flow of <strong>${fcf2025}M</strong>. We project this forward for 5 years, calculate a terminal value, and discount it all back to today.</p>

  <div class="assumptions-grid">
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Growth Rate (Yrs 1-5)</div>
      <div class="ac-value">{(growthRatePhase1 * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Estimated FCF growth. Reflects store expansion, steady demand, and modest margin expansion.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Terminal Growth</div>
      <div class="ac-value">{(growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Perpetual growth rate after year 5. Roughly in line with long-term GDP growth and inflation.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Discount Rate</div>
      <div class="ac-value">{(discountRate * 100).toFixed(0)}%</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Our required return. Built on a 4.18% 10-Yr Treasury plus a standard equity risk premium.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="assumption-card">
      <div class="ac-title">Shares Out.</div>
      <div class="ac-value">{sharesOutstanding}M</div>
      <div class="ac-desc">Basic shares outstanding as of the latest 10-K filing.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ PROJECTIONS TABLE ═══ -->
  <h2>Cash Flow Projections</h2>
  <p>Here is the year-by-year projection of Free Cash Flow, discounted back to present value (PV). All figures in millions USD.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th style="text-align:left">Period</th>
          <th>Projected FCF</th>
          <th>Discount Factor</th>
          <th>Present Value</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {projections.map((p, i) => (
          <tr>
            <td style="text-align:left">{p.year}</td>
            <td>${p.fcf.toFixed(0)}</td>
            <td>{Math.pow(1 + discountRate, i + 1).toFixed(3)}</td>
            <td>${p.pv.toFixed(0)}</td>
          </tr>
        ))}
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td style="text-align:left">Sum of PV (Yrs 1-5)</td>
          <td></td>
          <td></td>
          <td>${pvOfFCF.toFixed(0)}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- ═══ TERMINAL VALUE ═══ -->
  <h2>Terminal Value</h2>
  <p>We assume O'Reilly will continue to operate indefinitely after Year 5, growing cash flows at { (growthRateTerminal * 100).toFixed(1) }% per year. We use the Gordon Growth Model to calculate this terminal value, then discount it back to today.</p>

  <ul>
    <li>Year 6 FCF: ${terminalYearFCF.toFixed(0)}M</li>
    <li>Terminal Value: ${terminalValue.toFixed(0)}M</li>
    <li><strong>Present Value of Terminal Value: ${pvOfTerminalValue.toFixed(0)}M</strong></li>
  </ul>

  <!-- ═══ FINAL CALCULATION ═══ -->
  <h2>Enterprise Value to Equity Value</h2>
  <p>To find the value per share, we sum our PVs to get Enterprise Value, add cash, subtract debt, and divide by the share count.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">PV of FCF (Years 1-5)</td>
          <td>${pvOfFCF.toFixed(0)}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td style="text-align:left">PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>+${pvOfTerminalValue.toFixed(0)}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td style="text-align:left">Enterprise Value</td>
